CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 12, 1941, pg. 18, reads: "Pictured here are the young ladies who won prizes in bathing beauty contest last Friday sponsored by the Business and Professional Men's Association in Pittsburgh of their annual South Park picnic. Left to right: Miss Francis Moore of 628 Morgan Street who won 1st prize... - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Francis Moore wearing one-piece bathing suit and sash inscribed "Miss BPA 1941," holding first prize trophy for the Business and Professional Men's Association picnic beauty contest, South Park
